Sentencas: In this paper, niobium doping is evaluated as a means of enhancing the electrochemical performance of a Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM) perovskite structure cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) applications.
Titulo: Investigation into the effect of molybdenum-site substitution on the performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As the radius of Nb approximates that of Mo and exhibits +4/+5 mixed valences, its substitution is expected to improve material performance.
Titulo: Investigation into the effect of molybdenum-site substitution on the performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A series of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xNb5O6-delta (x = 0.05, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20) cathode materials are prepared and the phase structure, chemical compatibility, microstructure, electrical conductivity, polarization resistance and power generation are systematically characterized.
Titulo: Investigation into the effect of molybdenum-site substitution on the performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the series of samples, Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.4Nb0.10O6-delta (SFMNb0.10) exhibits the highest conductivity value of 30 S cm(-1) at 550 degrees C, and the lowest area specific resistance of 0.068 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. Furthermore, an anode-supported single cell incorporating a SFMNb0.10 cathode presents a maximum power density of 1102 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Investigation into the effect of molybdenum-site substitution on the performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore no obvious performance degradation is observed over 15 h at 750 degrees C with wet H-2 (3% H2O) as fuel and ambient air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Investigation into the effect of molybdenum-site substitution on the performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that SFMNb shows great promise as a novel cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Investigation into the effect of molybdenum-site substitution on the performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
